1
00:00:43,200 --> 00:00:43,759
Brigade Commander.

2
00:00:43,840 --> 00:00:44,439
A good match.

3
00:00:45,960 --> 00:00:46,679
A good match.

4
00:00:48,280 --> 00:00:50,159
She's a perfect match for my son.

5
00:00:52,920 --> 00:00:53,679
What?

6
00:00:54,320 --> 00:00:55,200
You don't agree?

7
00:00:55,799 --> 00:00:56,240
Brigade Commander.

8
00:00:56,520 --> 00:00:57,240
I agree, I agree.

9
00:00:57,600 --> 00:00:58,799
How could I possibly not agree?

10
00:00:58,799 --> 00:00:59,399
Right, brother-in-law?

11
00:01:00,439 --> 00:01:01,119
Yes, yes.

12
00:01:01,439 --> 00:01:01,880
I agree.

13
00:01:01,920 --> 00:01:02,719
Absolutely.

14
00:01:03,119 --> 00:01:04,840
As they say, like father, like son.

15
00:01:05,000 --> 00:01:05,799
For my daughter to marry

16
00:01:05,799 --> 00:01:06,640
the Brigade Commander's son,

17
00:01:07,040 --> 00:01:08,159
you honor me.

18
00:01:08,879 --> 00:01:09,560
You honor me.

19
00:01:10,200 --> 00:01:11,000
Let me toast you.

20
00:01:13,480 --> 00:01:13,879
Drink up.

21
00:01:14,680 --> 00:01:15,560
I'll drink first to show my respect.

22
00:01:19,400 --> 00:01:20,040
Good.

23
00:01:21,000 --> 00:01:21,760
This matter,

24
00:01:21,959 --> 00:01:22,560
it's settled then.

25
00:01:24,200 --> 00:01:24,920
In a few days,

26
00:01:25,159 --> 00:01:26,680
I'll send someone to your home to propose marriage.

27
00:01:27,319 --> 00:01:28,439
Wonderful, Brigade Commander.

28
00:01:28,680 --> 00:01:29,159
Brother-in-law.

29
00:01:29,359 --> 00:01:30,040
This is great news.

30
00:01:30,079 --> 00:01:31,680
The best news ever!

31
00:01:32,599 --> 00:01:33,359
It's a deal.

32
00:01:34,239 --> 00:01:34,840
Shuisheng,

33
00:01:35,280 --> 00:01:36,359
why are you just standing there?

34
00:01:40,200 --> 00:01:40,840
Reporting, Brigade Commander.

35
00:01:41,439 --> 00:01:42,560
Company Commander Shuisheng wants

36
00:01:42,760 --> 00:01:43,239
to congratulate you,

37
00:01:43,319 --> 00:01:43,920
to offer congratulations.

38
00:01:45,040 --> 00:01:45,719
Right, Company Commander?

39
00:01:47,840 --> 00:01:48,280
Yes.

40
00:01:49,280 --> 00:01:49,799
Brigade Commander,

41
00:01:50,040 --> 00:01:50,799
let me toast you.

42
00:01:52,519 --> 00:01:52,920
Good.

43
00:01:52,920 --> 00:01:53,599
Let's drink together.

44
00:01:53,959 --> 00:01:54,560
The joy is mutual.

45
00:02:06,200 --> 00:02:06,760
This girl,

46
00:02:06,959 --> 00:02:07,640
didn't even say a word.

47
00:02:07,879 --> 00:02:08,439
So rude.

48
00:02:08,439 --> 00:02:09,120
Brother-in-law,

49
00:02:09,360 --> 00:02:10,400
she went to get the food.

50
00:02:10,400 --> 00:02:11,120
To get the food.

51
00:02:23,120 --> 00:02:23,840
Anyone home?

52
00:02:23,840 --> 00:02:25,039
Coming, coming, coming!

53
00:02:26,719 --> 00:02:27,879
On a rainy day too.

54
00:02:27,960 --> 00:02:28,759
Such an impatient soul.

55
00:02:33,719 --> 00:02:34,319
Master.

56
00:02:34,479 --> 00:02:35,280
Did you miss me?

57
00:02:37,280 --> 00:02:39,039
Close the door from the outside.

58
00:02:42,520 --> 00:02:43,319
Dongsheng.

59
00:02:43,960 --> 00:02:44,879
Dongsheng is back!

60
00:02:45,240 --> 00:02:45,759
Auntie Xiaoling.

61
00:02:45,800 --> 00:02:46,680
You're back.

62
00:02:46,719 --> 00:02:47,159
Come on.

63
00:02:48,960 --> 00:02:49,759
What happened to you?

64
00:02:50,000 --> 00:02:50,520
It's nothing.

65
00:02:51,120 --> 00:02:52,080
Got hurt during training.

66
00:02:52,360 --> 00:02:53,159
It'll be fine in a couple of days.

67
00:02:53,439 --> 00:02:54,240
You okay?

68
00:02:54,400 --> 00:02:54,840
I'm fine.

69
00:02:55,159 --> 00:02:55,680
Come on, come on.

70
00:02:55,680 --> 00:02:56,080
Hurry, hurry.

71
00:02:56,639 --> 00:02:57,280
Auntie Xiaoling,

72
00:02:58,080 --> 00:02:59,639
Master won't let me into the house.

73
00:03:00,919 --> 00:03:02,000
With me here today,

74
00:03:02,080 --> 00:03:02,719
I'd like to see who dares

75
00:03:02,719 --> 00:03:03,560
keep you from coming in.

76
00:03:03,719 --> 00:03:04,120
Come on.

77
00:03:06,719 --> 00:03:07,240
What's this?

78
00:03:07,400 --> 00:03:07,840
Something I brought.

79
00:03:21,319 --> 00:03:21,960
Master.

80
00:03:22,280 --> 00:03:22,759
Look what I

81
00:03:22,759 --> 00:03:23,280
brought you.

82
00:03:24,680 --> 00:03:25,520
This is Guandong Yunpian,

83
00:03:25,919 --> 00:03:26,800
the finest tobacco leaves.

84
00:03:28,039 --> 00:03:28,599
What a coincidence.

85
00:03:29,919 --> 00:03:30,680
I quit.

86
00:03:35,080 --> 00:03:36,280
This is your favorite,

87
00:03:36,360 --> 00:03:36,840
roast chicken.

88
00:03:38,240 --> 00:03:39,919
I'm fasting these days.

89
00:03:43,319 --> 00:03:43,919
And this one,

90
00:03:44,960 --> 00:03:45,840
the finest tea leaves.

91
00:03:47,919 --> 00:03:49,080
The finest?

92
00:03:49,560 --> 00:03:50,599
How fine can it be?

93
00:03:52,520 --> 00:03:53,280
Let me put it this way.

94
00:03:53,840 --> 00:03:54,400
This tea,

95
00:03:54,639 --> 00:03:54,919
once you drink it,

96
00:03:54,919 --> 00:03:55,759
you won't even want to pee it out.

97
00:03:56,039 --> 00:03:56,360
I...

98
00:03:59,960 --> 00:04:00,840
Next time,

99
00:04:00,919 --> 00:04:02,759
just bring this one straight.

100
00:04:02,840 --> 00:04:03,520
All right.

101
00:04:03,840 --> 00:04:04,719
Look at that.

102
00:04:05,439 --> 00:04:07,199
Our Dongsheng has grown up.

103
00:04:07,479 --> 00:04:09,039
He even knows to honor his master now.

104
00:04:09,319 --> 00:04:09,719
All right.

105
00:04:09,759 --> 00:04:10,280
Let's go.

106
00:04:12,319 --> 00:04:12,759
Auntie Xiaoling.

107
00:04:12,759 --> 00:04:13,479
I have something for you too.

108
00:04:13,680 --> 00:04:14,680
Something for me?

109
00:04:15,039 --> 00:04:15,759
This is vanishing cream.

110
00:04:15,879 --> 00:04:16,439
It smells wonderful.

111
00:04:16,439 --> 00:04:16,920
Give it a sniff.

112
00:04:20,040 --> 00:04:20,639
And this one,

113
00:04:21,120 --> 00:04:21,800
from Yin-Yang Ferry,

114
00:04:22,079 --> 00:04:22,839
the finest silk.

115
00:04:29,279 --> 00:04:30,079
Lao Jiugui.

116
00:04:30,680 --> 00:04:31,399
Take a look.

117
00:04:31,959 --> 00:04:32,879
This fabric,

118
00:04:34,079 --> 00:04:34,759
what do you think?

119
00:04:35,160 --> 00:04:36,160
I dare not look, I dare not look.

120
00:04:36,160 --> 00:04:37,839
Is this something I can look at for free?

121
00:04:38,759 --> 00:04:40,279
There are nothing but dead folk here.

122
00:04:40,319 --> 00:04:42,079
You're dressing up so pretty for the ghosts?

123
00:04:42,279 --> 00:04:42,839
That's right.

124
00:04:43,199 --> 00:04:44,000
For the ghosts to see.

125
00:04:44,439 --> 00:04:45,720
For you, Lao Jiugui.

126
00:04:47,279 --> 00:04:47,920
Oh, by the way,

127
00:04:48,480 --> 00:04:49,079
Master,

128
00:04:50,079 --> 00:04:50,759
look what this is.

129
00:04:58,480 --> 00:04:59,560
Why so much money?

130
00:04:59,639 --> 00:05:00,800
Have you been gambling again?

131
00:05:01,199 --> 00:05:02,199
I haven't.

132
00:05:02,759 --> 00:05:03,360
Master,

133
00:05:03,720 --> 00:05:04,839
I quit that long ago.

134
00:05:05,560 --> 00:05:06,600
The Brigade Commander gave it to me.

135
00:05:06,800 --> 00:05:07,279
Besides,

136
00:05:08,199 --> 00:05:08,560
isn't all this

137
00:05:08,560 --> 00:05:09,279
thanks to you, Master?

138
00:05:09,720 --> 00:05:10,959
What's it got to do with me?

139
00:05:11,639 --> 00:05:12,959
Weren't you the one who caught them last night?

140
00:05:12,959 --> 00:05:13,360
This, this, this...

141
00:05:13,360 --> 00:05:14,279
What about last night?

142
00:05:14,839 --> 00:05:15,879
What happened last night?

143
00:05:16,120 --> 00:05:16,600
I have no idea.

144
00:05:16,800 --> 00:05:17,480
Don't play dumb with me.

145
00:05:17,879 --> 00:05:19,079
Last night...

146
00:05:21,279 --> 00:05:22,120
No wonder you

147
00:05:22,120 --> 00:05:23,319
only got back early this morning.

148
00:05:23,519 --> 00:05:24,560
So you went to the army camp.

149
00:05:24,560 --> 00:05:25,079
I didn't.

150
00:05:25,360 --> 00:05:26,519
Didn't you swear you'd never go?

151
00:05:26,519 --> 00:05:27,040
I didn't go.

152
00:05:27,360 --> 00:05:28,000
I really didn't...

153
00:05:31,439 --> 00:05:32,000
This, this, this...

154
00:05:32,000 --> 00:05:32,839
This wine is fine.

155
00:05:32,839 --> 00:05:33,959
One whiff goes straight to your head.

156
00:05:34,120 --> 00:05:34,879
I, I, I...

157
00:05:34,879 --> 00:05:36,199
I need to go lie down over there.

158
00:05:37,000 --> 00:05:38,680
Your master's only stubborn with his words,

159
00:05:38,680 --> 00:05:39,759
but everything else about him is soft.

160
00:05:39,879 --> 00:05:40,480
Auntie Xiaoling,

161
00:05:41,360 --> 00:05:42,160
have you ever thought about...

162
00:05:43,439 --> 00:05:44,319
Thought about what?

163
00:05:45,079 --> 00:05:45,879
becoming my master's wife?

164
00:05:52,160 --> 00:05:53,040
It's not something

165
00:05:53,040 --> 00:05:53,920
I can decide on my own.

166
00:05:55,279 --> 00:05:55,759
Understood.

167
00:05:56,319 --> 00:05:56,959
Leave it to me.

168
00:06:07,399 --> 00:06:08,160
Done sweeping?

169
00:06:18,319 --> 00:06:20,720
Which side did the sun rise from today?

170
00:06:21,920 --> 00:06:23,800
You're even reading books now?

171
00:06:26,160 --> 00:06:27,000
One should be seen in a new light

172
00:06:27,000 --> 00:06:28,199
after three days, Master.

173
00:06:31,240 --> 00:06:33,160
With no one to aid my lofty ambition,

174
00:06:33,360 --> 00:06:35,360
I'll tread the snow to the summit myself.

175
00:06:36,160 --> 00:06:37,000
So no one's helping?

176
00:06:37,279 --> 00:06:38,279
Right, right, no one.

177
00:06:39,000 --> 00:06:39,759
You climb up yourself.

178
00:06:39,879 --> 00:06:40,240
By myself.

179
00:06:40,600 --> 00:06:41,399
That's not what I meant.

180
00:06:41,399 --> 00:06:42,040
Master.

181
00:06:43,879 --> 00:06:44,519
Master.

182
00:06:45,720 --> 00:06:47,199
During my time away from Bone-Keeping Temple,

183
00:06:47,839 --> 00:06:49,000
I did some soul-searching.

184
00:06:49,560 --> 00:06:50,399
I realized what you said

185
00:06:50,480 --> 00:06:51,160
was absolutely right.

186
00:06:51,399 --> 00:06:52,959
I've said so many things.

187
00:06:53,319 --> 00:06:55,560
So which one of them

188
00:06:55,839 --> 00:06:56,480
do you think was right?

189
00:06:59,839 --> 00:07:00,560
This water...

190
00:07:01,680 --> 00:07:02,399
does it have any kick to it?

191
00:07:04,720 --> 00:07:05,639
Have some water.

192
00:07:06,240 --> 00:07:07,079
Water...

193
00:07:07,199 --> 00:07:08,920
has no kick to it.

194
00:07:16,360 --> 00:07:16,959
So...

195
00:07:17,839 --> 00:07:19,639
out of everything I told you,

196
00:07:20,680 --> 00:07:21,920
that's the only one

197
00:07:22,639 --> 00:07:23,399
you remembered?

198
00:07:23,600 --> 00:07:24,319
Right?

199
00:07:25,560 --> 00:07:26,439
Lao Jiugui!

200
00:07:27,600 --> 00:07:28,319
What are you doing?

201
00:07:28,480 --> 00:07:29,759
Are you ever going to stop?

202
00:07:30,279 --> 00:07:31,160
Auntie Xiaoling.

203
00:07:31,879 --> 00:07:32,600
Let me see.

204
00:07:32,959 --> 00:07:34,160
My arm was already...

205
00:07:35,120 --> 00:07:35,959
Are you okay?

206
00:07:36,920 --> 00:07:37,720
Auntie Xiaoling,

207
00:07:38,600 --> 00:07:39,480
it doesn't hurt anymore.

208
00:07:42,319 --> 00:07:43,680
Master, you're amazing!

209
00:07:44,639 --> 00:07:45,360
Want to learn?

210
00:07:45,600 --> 00:07:46,319
Yes.

211
00:07:47,920 --> 00:07:49,279
Then pour me some wine.

212
00:07:54,319 --> 00:07:56,360
Start reading from this line.

213
00:07:56,720 --> 00:07:57,600
Once you understand this line,

214
00:07:57,600 --> 00:07:58,519
you'll get it.

215
00:08:12,600 --> 00:08:13,279
Not bad.

216
00:08:24,000 --> 00:08:25,160
You little rascal!

217
00:08:34,080 --> 00:08:34,919
I'll stop, Master!

218
00:08:35,240 --> 00:08:36,000
I'll stop!

219
00:08:43,039 --> 00:08:44,360
Learning to use sneak attacks now, are we?

220
00:09:01,399 --> 00:09:02,200
Master!

221
00:09:02,200 --> 00:09:02,960
Master!

222
00:09:04,559 --> 00:09:05,159
Dongsheng!

223
00:09:05,559 --> 00:09:05,919
Dongsheng!

224
00:09:05,919 --> 00:09:06,559
Coming, coming!

225
00:09:06,679 --> 00:09:07,200
This is bad!

226
00:09:07,600 --> 00:09:07,960
Dongsheng.

227
00:09:07,960 --> 00:09:08,320
What's wrong?

228
00:09:08,399 --> 00:09:09,360
Something's gone wrong!

229
00:09:09,360 --> 00:09:09,720
What is it?

230
00:09:09,720 --> 00:09:10,399
Dongsheng.

231
00:09:11,159 --> 00:09:12,200
Who's this?

232
00:09:13,320 --> 00:09:13,799
Master.

233
00:09:14,000 --> 00:09:14,799
This is our Company Commander,

234
00:09:14,799 --> 00:09:15,279
Shuisheng.

235
00:09:16,159 --> 00:09:17,080
Hello, Commander Shui.

236
00:09:17,080 --> 00:09:18,720
You must be Dongsheng's Master.

237
00:09:18,720 --> 00:09:19,200
Yes.

238
00:09:19,759 --> 00:09:20,799
I pay my respects, sir.

239
00:09:20,799 --> 00:09:21,720
No need, no need.

240
00:09:21,960 --> 00:09:23,200
You're not my disciple.

241
00:09:23,200 --> 00:09:24,159
No need to bow.

242
00:09:24,679 --> 00:09:25,399
So what's going on?

243
00:09:25,799 --> 00:09:26,360
Well...

244
00:09:26,519 --> 00:09:27,080
It's nothing.

245
00:09:27,320 --> 00:09:27,799
Shuisheng.

246
00:09:28,080 --> 00:09:29,320
My Master isn't an outsider.

247
00:09:29,879 --> 00:09:30,399
It's just...

248
00:09:31,360 --> 00:09:32,039
The Brigade Commander led

249
00:09:32,039 --> 00:09:33,000
the troops to wipe out the bandits.

250
00:09:33,039 --> 00:09:33,960
That's a good thing.

251
00:09:34,080 --> 00:09:34,759
Why didn't you go?

252
00:09:36,320 --> 00:09:37,639
He sent me with the betrothal gifts

253
00:09:37,879 --> 00:09:38,879
to propose marriage at the Town Chief's.

254
00:09:40,440 --> 00:09:40,799
Well...

255
00:09:41,240 --> 00:09:42,960
Isn't that a good thing too?

256
00:09:45,759 --> 00:09:46,440
Master,

257
00:09:47,279 --> 00:09:48,000
Shuisheng, he...

258
00:09:48,159 --> 00:09:49,320
has his eye on someone else's bride.

259
00:09:51,080 --> 00:09:51,799
Don't talk nonsense.

260
00:09:52,559 --> 00:09:53,399
This kid

261
00:09:53,639 --> 00:09:55,240
doesn't look like that kind of person.

262
00:09:58,240 --> 00:09:59,240
He doesn't seem like it to me either.

263
00:10:00,759 --> 00:10:01,600
Dongsheng,

264
00:10:01,960 --> 00:10:02,639
what Dongsheng said

265
00:10:03,000 --> 00:10:03,360
is...

266
00:10:03,679 --> 00:10:04,480
actually true.

267
00:10:05,559 --> 00:10:06,200
Really?

268
00:10:07,320 --> 00:10:08,000
Shuisheng.

269
00:10:09,120 --> 00:10:09,759
Behind us...

270
00:10:10,039 --> 00:10:11,120
who's that in the carriage?

271
00:10:12,600 --> 00:10:13,360
She's the Daoist priestess the Brigade Commander invited

272
00:10:13,360 --> 00:10:14,519
to divine the marriage match.

273
00:10:14,879 --> 00:10:16,320
They say she can summon wind and rain

274
00:10:16,440 --> 00:10:17,320
and turn beans into soldiers.

275
00:10:18,039 --> 00:10:18,759
Then why didn't the Brigade Commander

276
00:10:18,919 --> 00:10:20,279
take her along to wipe out the bandits?

277
00:10:20,759 --> 00:10:21,879
A handful of bandits

278
00:10:21,960 --> 00:10:23,320
isn't worth such a fuss.

279
00:10:24,360 --> 00:10:25,440
My Master told me

280
00:10:25,879 --> 00:10:27,559
the bandits of Clear Wind Fort at Wild Fox Ridge

281
00:10:27,559 --> 00:10:28,519
are something of a righteous army.

282
00:10:29,200 --> 00:10:30,000
They rob the rich to help the poor.

283
00:10:30,159 --> 00:10:31,320
And with the common folk, it's

284
00:10:31,440 --> 00:10:32,039
all fair trade.

285
00:10:33,919 --> 00:10:34,799
Whatever, I don't care.

286
00:10:35,080 --> 00:10:36,200
I'm troubled enough as it is.

287
00:10:36,399 --> 00:10:37,399
Don't worry, brother.

288
00:10:38,279 --> 00:10:39,159
Watch me go in a bit

289
00:10:39,679 --> 00:10:40,480
and mess up

290
00:10:40,480 --> 00:10:41,360
this marriage for him.

291
00:10:42,720 --> 00:10:43,279
Really?

292
00:10:43,279 --> 00:10:44,200
Who are you underestimating?

293
00:10:44,200 --> 00:10:45,159
You can actually do that?

294
00:10:46,039 --> 00:10:46,679
Let me tell you,

295
00:10:46,679 --> 00:10:47,200
This past month,

296
00:10:47,360 --> 00:10:48,039
I've learned a lot

297
00:10:48,039 --> 00:10:48,759
from my Master.

298
00:10:49,879 --> 00:10:50,960
Then do you know Summoning Infernal Soldiers?

299
00:10:51,399 --> 00:10:52,600
Forget Ghost Soldiers.

300
00:10:53,120 --> 00:10:54,559
Even the Celestial Army,

301
00:10:54,679 --> 00:10:55,600
I can summon at will

302
00:10:55,879 --> 00:10:56,879
and dismiss with a wave.

303
00:10:59,799 --> 00:11:00,799
I'm not bragging,

304
00:11:01,080 --> 00:11:01,879
Last night,

305
00:11:01,879 --> 00:11:03,159
Chang'e invited me to the Moon Palace

306
00:11:03,519 --> 00:11:04,840
to eat spicy rabbit head.

307
00:11:06,559 --> 00:11:07,159
So it turns out

308
00:11:07,360 --> 00:11:08,519
Chang'e is a Sichuan girl.

309
00:11:16,399 --> 00:11:17,000
Brother-in-law.

310
00:11:17,440 --> 00:11:18,799
This Brigade Commander is so generous.

311
00:11:20,120 --> 00:11:20,639
Of course.

312
00:11:21,039 --> 00:11:21,679
Absolutely.

313
00:11:22,679 --> 00:11:24,279
And where is my in-law, the Brigade Commander?

314
00:11:24,840 --> 00:11:25,480
To answer you, madam,

315
00:11:25,840 --> 00:11:26,799
the Brigade Commander is off suppressing bandits.

316
00:11:27,480 --> 00:11:28,759
So he sent me to deliver the betrothal letter.

317
00:11:29,159 --> 00:11:29,600
Look at that.

318
00:11:30,399 --> 00:11:31,200
Just look at our Brigade Commander.

319
00:11:31,519 --> 00:11:32,759
For the sake of the nation,

320
00:11:33,159 --> 00:11:34,320
he toils heart and soul.

321
00:11:35,240 --> 00:11:36,799
Done with the pleasantries?

322
00:11:38,399 --> 00:11:39,440
Bring out the bride and groom.

323
00:11:56,720 --> 00:11:57,519
What are you standing there for?

324
00:11:58,080 --> 00:11:58,799
Go call Qiuying.
